        'MA.4.AR.1–3 — Multi-step problems, factors/multiples, prime/composite, patterns',
        'MA.4.FR.1–2 — Full fraction operations including fraction × whole number (ALL students need PM3 prep)',
        'MA.4.M, MA.4.DP — Conversions, elapsed time, line plots with fractions, perimeter',
        'MA.4.GR.1–2 — 2D classification, angle measurement, symmetry'
      ],
      strategies: [
        'Whole-class rigorous Tier 1 instruction with differentiated questioning and tiered tasks',
        'Math discourse: "Talk moves" — restate, add on, agree/disagree with evidence',
